                "name": "Spyhawk"
            },
            "notes": "Reopening.\r\n\r\nThe good:\r\n* weapon icons are easy to recognize even on long distance\r\n* color based on class availability is great\r\n\r\nThe less-good:\r\n* -weapon overlay too intrusive. Remove the white \"border\" but keep the translucent background (so we get a sense of where it touches the ground, which make it easier to pick up)- (done)\r\n* health, ammo and objective icon colors are less neonish that first try, but they still don't look fully integrated. Make them more wwish (see the shield icon, maybe use a similar white border with full background).\r\n\r\n-Consider also colouring the weapon icons similar to the player currently hold, so one would know which weapon should be \"pick up\" manually (to change weapon) or the one that would be quickly picked up for extra ammo.- (done)",
